<subSubSection box="[151,589,187,214]" pageId="2" pageNumber="239" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,937,151,214]" box="[151,589,187,214]" pageId="2" pageNumber="239">
(Adapted from 
<bibRefCitation author="Drew, R. A. I. &amp; Romig, M. C." box="[324,582,187,214]" pageId="2" pageNumber="239" refId="ref7235" refString="Drew, R. A. I. &amp; Romig, M. C. (2016) Keys to the tropical fruit flies (Tephritidae: Dacinae) of South-East Asia. CAB International, Wallingford, 487 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1079 / 9781780644196.0000" type="book" year="2016">Drew and Romig 2016</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="239" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,259,394]" pageId="2" pageNumber="239">
The 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Perkins" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[204,341,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Bactrocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrotibialis">
<emphasis box="[204,341,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="239">nigrotibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex was defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Drew, R. A. I. &amp; Romig, M. C." box="[639,920,259,286]" pageId="2" pageNumber="239" refId="ref7187" refString="Drew, R. A. I. &amp; Romig, M. C. (2013) Tropical fruit flies (Tephritidae: Dacinae) of South-East Asia. CAB International, Wallingford, 653 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1079 / 9781780640358.0000" type="book" year="2013">Drew and Romig (2013)</bibRefCitation>
to contain mostly black species without redbrown areas on the scutum, a narrow costal band, face black or with large facial spots and legs with all femora at least apically black, the fore and mid femora often mostly so. Proposed largely as an aid to identification, the complex is not necessarily monophyletic or inclusive.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
